           </svg>
           <div class="flex flex-col">
             <span class="text-[10px] uppercase tracking-wider font-bold text-amber-600/60 dark:text-amber-400/60 leading-none mb-0.5">Created by</span>
             <span class="text-sm font-bold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-200 group-hover:text-amber-600 dark:group-hover:text-amber-400 transition-colors leading-none">@kaitranntt</span>
           </div>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="p-8 space-y-6">
      <!-- What is CCS -->
      <div class="p-5 rounded-lg bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-500/10 to-orange-500/10 border border-amber-500/20">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold font-sans text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mb-2 flex items-center gap-2">
          <svg class="w-5 h-5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
            <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/>
            <path d="M12 16v-4M12 8h.01"/>
          </svg>
          What is CCS?
        </h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 mb-3">
          <strong>CCS (Claude Code Switch)</strong> is a wrapper around Claude Code that lets you:
        </p>
        <div class="mb-3 px-3 py-2 bg-amber-500/10 rounded-lg border border-amber-500/20 text-xs text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
          <span class="font-bold text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400">New:</span> Zero-config OAuth support for <strong class="text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-300">Gemini</strong>, <strong class="text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-300">Codex</strong>, and <strong class="text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-300">Antigravity</strong> (via CLIProxyAPI)!
        </div>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-2 text-xs text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-amber-500 dark:text-amber-400" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/>
            </svg>
            <span>Switch between multiple Claude accounts & other providers (GLM, Kimi)</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-amber-500 dark:text-amber-400" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/>
            </svg>
            <span>Use cost-optimized models (GLM - 81% cheaper)</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-amber-500 dark:text-amber-400" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/>
            </svg>
            <span>Quick task delegation with -p flag</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-amber-500 dark:text-amber-400" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/>
            </svg>
            <span>Run parallel workflows in multiple terminals</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Installation -->
      <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-amber-500/20 text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 font-bold text-lg border-2 border-amber-500/50 flex items-center justify-center">
          1
        </div>
        <div class="flex-1">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold font-sans text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mb-2">Install CCS</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mb-3">Install globally after you've set up ClaudeKit:</p>
          <div class="bg-surface-100 dark:bg-[#0D0D0D] rounded-lg p-4 border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700 font-mono text-sm">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-2 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
              <span class="text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400">$</span>
              <div class="flex-1">
                <div>npm install -g @kaitranntt/ccs</div>
                <div class="text-slate-500 mt-2"># Verify installation</div>
                <div class="mt-1">ccs --version</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Usage -->
      <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-orange-500/20 text-orange-600 dark:text-orange-400 font-bold text-lg border-2 border-orange-500/50 flex items-center justify-center">
          2
        </div>
        <div class="flex-1">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold font-sans text-orange-600 dark:text-orange-400 mb-2">Use CCS Instead of claude</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mb-3">Now use <code class="px-1 py-0.5 bg-slate-200 dark:bg-slate-800 rounded font-mono text-orange-600 dark:text-orange-400">ccs</code> commands instead of <code class="px-1 py-0.5 bg-slate-200 dark:bg-slate-800 rounded font-mono">claude</code>:</p>

          <!-- Basic usage -->
          <div class="space-y-3">
            <div class="bg-surface-100 dark:bg-slate-950 rounded-lg p-4 border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700">
              <div class="text-xs font-medium text-orange-600 dark:text-orange-400 mb-2">Interactive Mode:</div>
              <div class="bg-white dark:bg-[#0D0D0D] rounded p-2 border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700 font-mono text-xs">
                <code class="text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">ccs</code>
                <div class="text-slate-500 mt-1"># Start interactive Claude Code with your default account</div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-surface-100 dark:bg-slate-950 rounded-lg p-4 border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700">
              <div class="text-xs font-medium text-orange-600 dark:text-orange-400 mb-2">Quick Delegation (Power Feature!):</div>
              <div class="bg-white dark:bg-[#0D0D0D] rounded p-2 border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700 font-mono text-xs space-y-2">
                <div>
                  <code class="text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">ccs -p "Using ui-ux-pro-max skill, create yoga landing page"</code>
                  <div class="text-slate-500 mt-1"># One-shot: AI does the task and exits</div>
                </div>
                <div class="pt-2 border-t border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700">
                  <code class="text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">ccs glm -p "add tests for all components"</code>
                  <div class="text-slate-500 mt-1"># Use GLM (81% cheaper) for simple tasks</div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-surface-100 dark:bg-slate-950 rounded-lg p-4 border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700">
              <div class="text-xs font-medium text-orange-600 dark:text-orange-400 mb-2">Multi-Account Setup:</div>
              <div class="bg-white dark:bg-[#0D0D0D] rounded p-2 border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700 font-mono text-xs space-y-2">
                <div>
                  <div class="text-slate-500 mb-0.5 opacity-80"># 1. Set up a Claude profile</div>
                  <code class="text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 font-semibold">ccs auth create work-claude</code>
                </div>
                <div>
                  <div class="text-slate-500 mb-0.5 opacity-80"># 2. Set up a Gemini profile</div>
                  <code class="text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 font-semibold">ccs auth create my-gemini</code>
                </div>
                <div class="pt-2 border-t border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800 mt-1">
                  <span class="text-slate-500"># Switch instantly:</span>
                  <div class="mt-1">
                    <span class="text-orange-600 dark:text-orange-400">ccs work-claude</span> <span class="text-slate-400 text-[10px] mx-1">|</span> <span class="text-orange-600 dark:text-orange-400">ccs my-gemini</span>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Pro Tips -->
      <div class="p-5 rounded-lg bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-500/10 to-yellow-500/10 border border-amber-500/20">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-bold font-sans text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
          <svg class="w-5 h-5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
            <path d="M12 2l3.09 6.26L22 9.27l-5 4.87 1.18 6.88L12 17.77l-6.18 3.25L7 14.14 2 9.27l6.91-1.01L12 2z"/>
          </svg>
          Why Use CCS?
        </h3>
        <div class="space-y-2 text-xs text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-amber-500 dark:text-amber-400 mt-0.5">ðŸ’°</span>
            <div>
              <strong class="text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">Save Money:</strong> Use GLM for simple tasks (tests, linting, documentation) - 81% cheaper than Claude
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-amber-500 dark:text-amber-400 mt-0.5">âš¡</span>
            <div>
              <strong class="text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">Work/Personal Split:</strong> Keep separate contexts for work and personal projects
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-amber-500 dark:text-amber-400 mt-0.5">ðŸš€</span>
            <div>
              <strong class="text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">Quick Delegation:</strong> Use <code class="px-1 py-0.5 bg-slate-200 dark:bg-slate-800 rounded font-mono">-p</code> flag for fire-and-forget tasks
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-amber-500 dark:text-amber-400 mt-0.5">ðŸ”„</span>
            <div>
              <strong class="text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">No Usage Limits:</strong> Hit your limit? Switch to another account or provider (like GLM) instantly
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

